{"type":"data","nodes":[{"type":"data","data":[{"debug":1},true],"uses":{}},{"type":"data","data":[{"zotero":1,"inscriptions":5},{"title":2,"date":3,"citation":4},"Le sculture da Alesa","2009","\u003Cspan>Elisa Chiara Portale, «Le sculture da Alesa», in \u003Ci>Alaisa-Halaesa. Scavi e ricerche (1970-2007)\u003C/i>, a c. di G. Scibona e G. Tigano (Messina: Sicania, 2009), 67–92\u003C/span>",[6,128],{"file":7,"uri":7,"title":8,"status":9,"editionAuthor":11,"type":12,"objectType":16,"material":20,"condition":24,"layoutDesc":25,"handNote":32,"date":46,"places":51,"geo":61,"provenance":53,"provenanceGeo":65,"country":68,"region":69,"settlement":53,"repository":70,"idno":74,"textLang":77,"tmNumber":81,"facsimile":82,"letterHeights":89,"publications":90,"zotero":100,"keywords":110,"html":120,"bibl":121},"ISic000768","Dedication by a sevir to Concordia",{"_":10},"edited",null,{"_":13,"ana":14,"ref":15},"dedication","#function.dedication","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/88.html",{"_":17,"ana":18,"ref":19},"base","#object.base","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/57.html",{"_":21,"ana":22,"ref":23},"marble (white)","#material.stone.marble","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html","",{"layout":26},{"p":27,"rs":28,"damage":24},"The epigraphic face is preserved for a width of 12.5 cm, with two lines of Latin letters filling the available field.",{"_":29,"ana":30,"ref":31},"chiselled","#execution.chiselled","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"lettering":33,"dimensions":34},"The letters are tall, neatly cut and closely spaced (height c.30mm), and words are separated by simple triangular interpuncts. The letters are lightly serifed. E is tall and narrow, T has a curved cross-bar, rising to the right.",[35,42],{"type":36,"l":37,"from":38,"to":39,"h":40,"unit":41},"letterHeight","Line 1-2","line1","line2","30","mm",{"type":43,"l":44,"from":38,"to":39,"h":45,"unit":41},"interlinear","Interlineation line 1 to 2","?",{"_":47,"notBefore":48,"notAfter":49,"precision":50},"Late 1st century CE, or 2nd century CE",51,200,"low",[52,56],{"_":53,"type":54,"ref":55},"Halaesa","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462225",{"_":57,"type":58,"ref":59,"offset":60},"Castel di Tusa","modern","http://sws.geonames.org/2525099","near",[62],[63,64],37.99907,14.26197,[66,67],37.998047,14.262635,"Italy","Sicily",{"_":71,"role":72,"ref":73},"Antiquarium e sito archeologico di Halaesa ","museum","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/053",{"_":75,"type":76},"ME 20226","inventory",{"_":78,"mainLang":79,"languages":80},"Latin","la",[78],"175722",{"n":83,"url":84,"height":85,"width":86,"desc":87,"surfaceType":88},"screen","ISic000768_tiled.tif","3395px","7360px","Photo J. Prag, courtesy Soprintendenza di Messina","front",[],[91,92,93,94,95,96,97,98,99],"L'année épigraphique: revue des publications épigraphiques relatives a l'antiquité romaine., 1888-","Scibona, 1971, Epigraphica Halaesina I","Manganaro, 1988, La Sicilia da Sesto Pompeo a Diocleziano","Manganaro, 1989, Iscrizioni Latine nuove e vecchie della Sicilia","Facella, 2006, Alesa Arconidea: ricerche su un'antica città della Sicilia tirrenica","Scibona, 2008, The Epigraphs","Portale, 2009, Le sculture da Alesa","Prestianni Giallombardo, 2012, Spazio pubblico e memoria civica. Le epigrafi dall'agora di Alesa","Prag and Tigano, 2017, Alesa Archonidea: il lapidarium",[101,102,103,104,105,106,107,108,109],"R46KDTZX","UISW82JC","RZSFKACR","EZMBJ6GN","J4XWZPV6","6GFVUASD","BCIMMIKZ","CJISRIUV","MI64NB9L",[111,112,113,13,17,21,114,115,116,117,114,118,119,79],"isic000768","dedication by a sevir to concordia",{"_":10},"halaesa","castel di tusa","italy","sicily","antiquarium e sito archeologico di halaesa","latin","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>Conco]ṛdiae · Aug[ustae\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ethus · sev[ir\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"author":122,"date":3,"citedRange":123,"ptr":124,"ref":126,"title":2,"citation":4},"Portale","85-87",{"target":125},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/BCIMMIKZ",{"_":127,"target":127},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001670",{"file":129,"uri":129,"title":130,"status":131,"editionAuthor":11,"type":132,"objectType":133,"material":136,"condition":24,"layoutDesc":137,"handNote":141,"date":153,"places":158,"geo":161,"provenance":53,"provenanceGeo":163,"country":68,"region":69,"settlement":53,"repository":166,"idno":167,"textLang":169,"tmNumber":171,"facsimile":172,"letterHeights":177,"publications":178,"zotero":180,"keywords":182,"html":186,"bibl":187},"ISic000804","Dedication of a statue to Ceres, by Iulius Acilius Hermes, sevir",{"_":10},{"_":13,"ana":14,"ref":15},{"_":134,"ana":135,"ref":19},"statue base","#object.statue_base",{"_":21,"ana":22,"ref":23},{"layout":138},{"p":139,"rs":140,"damage":24},"The Latin text is engraved over two lines (letters c.20 mm high, but of uneven height), to a maximum length of 52 cm.",{"_":29,"ana":30,"ref":31},{"lettering":142,"dimensions":143}," The letters show some irregularity, with fairly pronounced serifs, and lengthy tails to the letter R. The first two words are separated from the rest by a space; an interpunct is visible at the end of the dedicant’s name, and the final abbreviated phrase is separated from the rest by a large hedera (ivy leaf). The letter I in line 1 is frequently taller than the rest (but so too is the first L in line 1); the final I of line 1 is somewhat irregularly carved.",[144,147,150],{"type":36,"l":145,"from":38,"to":38,"h":146,"unit":41},"Line 1","18-25",{"type":36,"l":148,"from":39,"to":39,"h":149,"unit":41},"Line 2","19-23",{"type":43,"l":151,"from":38,"to":39,"h":152,"unit":41},"Interlineation lines 1-2","7-15",{"_":154,"notBefore":155,"notAfter":156,"evidence":157},"Statue can be dated stylistically to the late Antonine period (i.e. the 180s or 190s CE), and the text is compatible with such a date.",180,199,"context",[159,160],{"_":53,"type":54,"ref":55},{"_":57,"type":58,"ref":59,"offset":60},[162],[63,64],[164,165],37.998037,14.262643,{"_":71,"role":72,"ref":73},{"_":168,"type":76},"ME 20194",{"_":78,"mainLang":79,"languages":170},[78],"175724",{"n":83,"url":173,"height":174,"width":175,"desc":176,"surfaceType":88},"ISic000804_tiled.tif","1949px","4512px","Photo J. Prag courtesy Soprintendenza BBCCAA di Messina",[],[91,92,93,179,97,98,99],"Scibona, 2008, Statuary",[101,102,103,181,107,108,109],"EQC3W4UU",[183,184,185,13,134,21,114,115,116,117,114,118,119,79],"isic000804","dedication of a statue to ceres, by iulius acilius hermes, sevir",{"_":10},"\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Cereri sacr(um) \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\">(vac.1)\u003C/span> Iulius Acilius Her-\u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>mes · pro honor(e) seviratus ❦ d(eae) d(onum) d(edit) \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"author":122,"date":3,"citedRange":188,"ptr":189,"ref":190,"title":2,"citation":4},"80-87 fig.7",{"target":125},{"_":127,"target":127}],"uses":{"params":["slug"]}}]}
